people%20visited%20US%20restaurants%2C%20at%20least%20one%20person%20at%20the%20table%20or%20bar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhich-fast-food-chain-has-best-fries-south-review-photos-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eordered%20fries%3C%2Fa%3E%20nearly%2014%25%20of%20the%20time%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.simplotfoods.com%2Fblog%2Fnational-fry-day%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarket%20research%20group%20Circana%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20formerly%20NPD%20Group%2C%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20restaurants%20used%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeef-tallow-skincare-tiktok-acne-moisturizer-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etallow%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20rendered%20beef%20fat%2C%20to%20cook%20fries.%20It%20was%20responsible%20for%20the%20signature%2C%20rich%20taste%20of%20McDonald's%20fries%20as%20well%20as%20those%20from%20other%20major%20chains%20like%20Arby's%2C%20Burger%20King%2C%20and%20Wendy's.%20Then%2C%20amid%20the%20demonization%20of%20fats%20(later%20discovered%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2Fsections%2Fthetwo-way%2F2016%2F09%2F13%2F493739074%2F50-years-ago-sugar-industry-quietly-paid-scientists-to-point-blame-at-fat%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efunded%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20sugar%20industry)%2C%20we%20invented%20an%20alternative.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fvegetable-oil-vs-canola-oil%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECanola%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20short%20for%20Canadian%20oil%2C%20low%20acid%2C%20is%20made%20from%20the%20rapeseed%20plant%2C%20which%20was%20originally%20used%20to%20light%20lamps%20and%20lubricate%20machinery.%20After%20World%20War%20II%2C%20there%20was%20less%20need%20for%20machine%20oil%2C%20and%20Canadian%20researchers%20tried%20to%20find%20another%20use%20for%20the%20crop%2C%20which%20Canada%20leads%20the%20world%20in%20producing.%20They%20eventually%20created%20the%20edible%20and%20shelf-stable%20product%20we%20use%20today.%20By%20the%20'90s%2C%20the%20fast-food%20giants%20swapped%20their%20tallow%20supply%20for%20canola%2C%20often%20blended%20with%20other%20oils.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrench%20fries%20are%20crucial%20in%20how%20many%20restaurants%20balance%20their%20budgets.%20Ingredients%20for%20a%20typical%20burger%20might%20cost%20a%20restaurant%20about%2030%25%20of%20its%20menu%20price%2C%20but%20fries%20are%20closer%20to%2020%25.%20Even%20before%20Trump%20began%20implementing%20tariffs%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-equity-investing-billions-into-restaurants-fast-casuals-boom-bust-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20industry%20was%20struggling%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20as%20food%20prices%20rose%2C%20people%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshoppers-spending-less-retailers-brands-cutting-prices-economy-explained-why-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espending%20less%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20eating%20out%20less%2C%20and%20buying%20fewer%20fries.%20In%20October%2C%20Lamb%20Weston%2C%20which%20says%20it%20supplies%2080%25%20of%20America's%20fast-food%20fries%2C%20closed%20a%20production%20plant%20in%20Washington%2C%20reducing%20its%20production%20by%20about%205%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20fry%20consumption%20has%20dropped%2C%20restaurants%20have%20relied%20on%20the%20menu%20staple%20to%20balance%20out%20the%20skyrocketing%20costs%20of%20other%20ingredients%2C%20like%20beef%20(up%20over%2040%25%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years)%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fegg-prices-expensive-avian-bird-flu-changing-tastes-cage-free-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeggs%3C%2Fa%3E%20(up%20nearly%20100%25%20over%20the%20same%20period).%20A%20major%20increase%20in%20the%20cost%20of%20cooking%20oil%2C%20which%20has%20already%20jumped%20roughly%2050%25%20in%20cost%20since%202020%2C%20is%20likely%20to%20cause%20a%20crisis%20for%20your%20side%20of%20fries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20price%20of%20canola%20will%20rise%2C%20and%20that%20price%20increase%20will%20be%20passed%20along%20to%20all%20the%20different%20participants%20along%20the%20value%20chain%20%E2%80%94%20from%20the%20wholesale%20buyers%20to%20the%20restaurateurs%20to%20the%20final%20consumer%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Henry%20An%2C%20a%20professor%20and%20the%20chair%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Resource%20Economics%20and%20Environmental%20Sociology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Alberta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20believes%20that%20both%20countries%20will%20bear%20some%20of%20the%20burden.%20%26quot%3BThe%20canola%20sector%20in%20Canada%20doesn't%20have%20many%20short-term%20options%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20finding%20new%20buyers%2C%20and%20crop%20planting%20decisions%20have%20already%20been%20made%20for%20the%20most%20part.%20There's%20going%20to%20be%20some%20economic%20pain%20if%20these%20tariffs%20stay%20in%20place%20for%20a%20sustained%20period%20of%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20say%20how%20much%20the%20price%20of%20fries%20might%20increase%20%E2%80%94%20importers%20may%20choose%20to%20absorb%20some%20of%20the%20cost%20instead%20of%20passing%20it%20on%20to%20their%20restaurant%20customers%2C%20and%20restaurants%20can%20choose%20to%20absorb%20costs%20or%20pivot%20their%20supply%20network%20to%20avoid%20increasing%20the%20price%20for%20diners.%20But%20some%20costs%20will%20inevitably%20trickle%20down%3A%20During%20the%20five-year%20period%20that%20vegetable%20oil%20prices%20rose%20by%2050%25%2C%20the%20average%20menu%20price%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-new-marketing-billboards-that-smell-like-its-french-fries-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%20french%20fries%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20up%20134%25%2C%20from%20%241.79%20in%202019%20to%20%244.19%20in%202024%2C%20TheStreet%20found%20in%20an%20analysis.%20To%20be%20sure%2C%20rising%20labor%20costs%20and%20inflation%20also%20played%20a%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERestaurateurs%20have%20three%20choices%20to%20deal%20with%20significant%20cost%20increases%3A%20eat%20the%20cost%20and%20make%20less%20profit%2C%20pass%20the%20cost%20on%20to%20customers%20by%20raising%20menu%20prices%2C%20or%20change%20ingredients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20return%20to%20animal%20fats%20has%20been%20embraced%20by%20chefs%20over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20and%20more%20may%20follow%20suit.%20Amid%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fare-seed-oils-dangerous-for-your-health-inflammation-evidence-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebacklash%20to%20seed%20oil%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20National%20Restaurant%20Association%20says%20there's%20been%20increased%20interest%20in%20tallow%20from%20their%20members.%20But%20it's%20not%20a%20cost-saving%20solution.%20A%2035-pound%20bucket%20can%20range%20from%20%2460%20to%20%24119%2C%20while%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20canola%20or%20soybean%20oil%20averages%20%2440.%20Some%20pricier%20restaurants%20fry%20their%20fries%20in%20duck%20fat%2C%20which%20is%20even%20more%20expensive.%20Duckfat%2C%20a%20restaurant%20in%20Portland%2C%20uses%20duck%20fat%20and%20charges%20%248%20for%20a%20small%20fry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShifting%20to%20animal%20fats%20would%20transform%20fries%20from%20an%20everyday%20indulgence%2C%20something%20added%20to%20a%20child's%20meal%20without%20much%20thought%2C%20into%20a%20special%20treat%2C%20from%20the%20league%20of%20pizza%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fare-hot-dogs-better-in-air-fryer-or-on-grill%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehot%20dogs%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20ranks%20of%20lattes%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Favocados-eggs-toast-expensive-tariffs-mexico-luxury-flu-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavocado%20toast%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20avoiding%20canola%2C%20some%20restaurants%20might%20start%20to%20stretch%20its%20use.%20Cooks%20usually%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-panics-open-secret-cooking-oil-fuel-chemical-tanks-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efryer%20oil%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20once%20it's%20too%20cloudy%20with%20bits%20of%20food%20or%20is%20breaking%20down%20from%20excessive%20use%2C%20they%20will%20drain%20the%20fryers.%20Each%20time%20oil%20is%20used%2C%20the%20smoke%20point%20lowers%2C%20eventually%20giving%20off%20an%20unpleasant%20smell%20and%20taste%2C%20producing%20darker%20food%2C%20and%20emitting%20more%20smoke.%20But%20there%20are%20ways%20that%20restaurants%20can%20extend%20the%20life%20of%20their%20oil%20without%20making%20the%20food%20taste%20bad.%20Samantha%20Fore's%20oil%20supplier%20has%20the%20fryer%20at%20her%20restaurant%20Tuk%20Tuk%20Snack%20Shop%20in%20Lexington%2C%20Kentucky%2C%20hooked%20up%20to%20two%20tanks.%20One%20extracts%20bad%20oil%2C%20and%20the%20other%20pumps%20in%20fresh%20stuff%20as%20needed.%20The%20used%20oil%20is%20picked%20up%20by%20the%20supplier%20and%20transformed%20into%20biofuel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20soybean%20oil%20blend%20she%20uses%20costs%20her%20about%20%2415%2C000%20a%20year.%20Even%20though%20her%20supplier%20uses%20domestic%20oil%2C%20she's%20nervous%20that%20the%20tax%20on%20imported%20oil%20could%20drive%20up%20the%20demand%20and%20price%20of%20domestic%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBetween%20the%20potential%20of%20what%20could%20happen%20to%20oil%20and%20wine%2C%20it's%20enough%20to%20put%20any%20restaurant%20owner%20into%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20a%20tailspin%2C%26quot%3B%20Fore%20says.%20But%20she%20can't%20keep%20raising%20prices.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20aren't%20going%20to%20want%20to%20pay%2015%20bucks%20for%20a%20side%20of%20french%20fries%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20market%20sensitivity%20there%20that%20we%20might%20not%20be%20able%20to%20meet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20she'll%20have%20to%20reconsider%20her%20menu%20or%20purchasing%20options.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20what%20we've%20had%20to%20do%20with%20eggs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BTo%20see%20this%20much%20volatility%20and%20not%20be%20able%20to%20forecast%20effectively%2C%20the%20little%20decisions%20have%20such%20a%20huge%20domino%20effect%20on%20how%20we%20survive%20in%20a%20very%20uncertain%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECatherine%20Mendelsohn%2C%20the%20chief%20operating%20officer%20of%20Sunnyside%20Restaurant%20Group%2C%20says%20her%20company%20also%20uses%20a%20machine%20to%20help%20extend%20the%20life%20of%20cooking%20oil%20at%20the%20burger%20and%20fry%20shop%20Good%20Stuff%20Eatery.%20The%20restaurant's%20%2435%2C000%20three-chamber%20fryer%20has%20a%20filtering%20system%20that%20cleans%20the%20oil%20during%20operation%20and%20reduces%20cooking%20oil%20costs.%20Even%20though%20Good%20Stuff%20spends%20about%20%2410%2C000%20a%20year%20on%20canola%20at%20each%20location%2C%20Mendelsohn%20isn't%20worried%20about%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20fries%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20big%20hit%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BCountries%20have%20to%20protect%20their%20borders.%20If%20that's%20a%20reason%20for%20the%20tariffs%2C%20temporarily%20until%20things%20get%20under%20control%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20that's%20a%20bad%20thing.%26quot%3B%20She%20plans%20to%20absorb%20the%20cost%20of%20any%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%2C%20DC-based%20restaurant%20group%20Knead%20Hospitality%20%2B%20Design%20operates%2010%20restaurants%2C%20four%20of%20which%20use%20an%20estimated%201%2C200%20pounds%20each%20of%20canola%20oil%20a%20month%20to%20make%20fries.%20Christian%20Plotczyk%2C%20its%20director%20of%20culinary%20operations%2C%20says%20the%20company%20has%20a%20contract%20with%20a%20guaranteed%20price%20for%20oil%20through%20the%20end%20of%202025.%20But%20if%20tariffs%20are%20still%20in%20place%20by%20then%2C%20it%20would%20have%20to%20look%20at%20switching%20oils.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemetri%20Tsolakis%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Xenia%20Greek%20Hospitality%2C%20also%20prefers%20to%20try%20a%20different%20oil%20rather%20than%20raise%20prices.%20He%20says%20the%20company%20spends%20%24123%2C760%20a%20year%20on%20canola%20oil%20for%20fryers%20at%20its%20seven%20restaurants%20around%20Boston.%20If%20the%20tariffs%20on%20canola%20oil%20happen%2C%20he%20might%20switch%20to%20sugarcane%20oil%2C%20which%20costs%20twice%20as%20much%20as%20canola%20but%20can%20last%20up%20to%20four%20times%20as%20long%20in%20his%20fryer's%20advanced%20filtration%20system%20(he%20calls%20it%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Cadillac%20of%20fryers%26quot%3B).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trouble%20with%20trying%20out%20alternative%20oils%2C%20though%2C%20is%20that%20there%20may%20not%20be%20enough%20supply%20for%20every%20restaurant%20making%20fries%20in%20canola%20to%20easily%20swap.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fbeef-tallow-seed-oils-maha-b60eecb9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndustry%20experts%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20already%20sounding%20the%20alarm%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20beef%20tallow%20supply%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20given%20how%20much%20canola%20is%20used%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20imagine%20a%20similar%20issue%20if%20restaurants%20all%20try%20to%20switch%20to%20soybean%2C%20sugarcane%2C%20or%20some%20other%20oil.%20Canola%20also%20provides%20a%20mouthwatering%20golden%20color%20to%20fries%20that%20other%20oils%20fail%20to%20achieve%2C%20so%20a%20change%20could%20disappoint%20diners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20stage%2C%20it's%20impossible%20to%20know%20how%20everything%20will%20shake%20out.%20%26quot%3BEconomists%20like%20to%20predict%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20An%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Alberta%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20even%20we%20are%20sensible%20enough%20to%20admit%20that%20we%20don't%20really%20have%20a%20clue%20what's%20going%20to%20unfold.%26quot%3B%20For%20now%2C%20Trump's%20trade%20war%20is%20poised%20to%20make%20freedom%20fries%20far%20from%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fcorey-mintz%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ECorey%20Mintz%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20food%20reporter%20focusing%20on%20the%20intersection%20of%20food%2C%20economics%2C%20and%20labor.%20He%20is%20also%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Next%20Supper%3A%20The%20End%20Of%20Restaurants%20As%20We%20Knew%20Them%2C%20And%20What%20Comes%20After.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trade-war-canada-tariffs-french-fries-canola-oil-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744964401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67fd6b5d3fe8d39283630989%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trade-war-canada-tariffs-french-fries-canola-oil-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President%20Donald%20Trump%20loves%20McDonald's%20fries.%20His%20tariffs%20don't.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Corey%20Mintz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A164%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trade-war-canada-tariffs-french-fries-canola-oil-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22It's%20a%20confusing%20mess%20to%20compare%20the%20alphabet%20soup%20of%20AI%20models%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Altman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679d36f77bb3f854015b6416%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223999%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIt's%20getting%20harder%20to%20compare%20AI%20models.%3Cp%3EMichael%20M.%20Santiago%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20AI%20models%2C%20and%20it%20can%20be%20tricky%20to%20know%20which%20are%20best.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETech%20companies%20often%20use%20%26quot%3Bbenchmarks%26quot%3B%20to%20measure%20how%20an%20AI%20model%20performs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20industry%20observers%20are%20becoming%20increasingly%20wary%20of%20benchmark%20reliability.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20pick%20the%20best%20AI%20to%20help%20you%20in%20work%20and%20life.%20What%20about%20GPT-4o%2C%204.5%2C%204.1%2C%20o1%2C%20o1-pro%2C%20o3-mini%2C%20or%20o3-mini-high%3F%20If%20not%20OpenAI%2C%20you%20can%20go%20for%20one%20of%20the%20many%20models%20put%20out%20by%20Meta%2C%20Google%2C%20or%20Anthropic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20year%20has%20already%20seen%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20model%20releases%20from%20major%20AI%20companies%2C%20and%20it%20can%20be%20confusing%20to%20decipher%20which%20really%20have%20a%20competitive%20edge.%20Developers%20of%20most%20of%20those%20releases%20claimed%20their%20AI%20had%20superior%20%26quot%3Bbenchmark%26quot%3B%20results%20in%20some%20way.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20way%20of%20comparing%20them%20has%20faced%20concerns%20that%20they%20might%20not%20be%20rigorous%20or%20reliable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20Meta%20released%20two%20new%20models%20in%20its%20Llama%20family%20that%20it%20said%20delivered%20%26quot%3Bbetter%20results%26quot%3B%20than%20comparably%20sized%20models%20from%20Google%20and%20Mistral.%20However%2C%20Meta%20then%20faced%20accusations%20that%20it%20had%20gamed%20a%20benchmark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELMArena%2C%20an%20AI%20benchmark%20that%20crowdsources%20user%20votes%20on%20model%20performance%2C%20said%20that%20Meta%20%26quot%3Bshould%20have%20made%20it%20clearer%26quot%3B%20that%20it%20had%20submitted%20a%20version%20of%20Llama%204%20Maverick%20that%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bcustomized%26quot%3B%20to%20perform%20better%20for%20its%20testing%20format.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMeta's%20interpretation%20of%20our%20policy%20did%20not%20match%20what%20we%20expect%20from%20model%20providers%2C%26quot%3B%20LMArena%20said%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Flmarena_ai%2Fstatus%2F1909397817434816562%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%20post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Meta%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3B'Llama-4-Maverick-03-26-Experimental'%20is%20a%20chat-optimized%20version%20we%20experimented%20with%20that%20also%20performs%20well%20on%20LMArena.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20now%20released%20our%20open%20source%20version%20and%20will%20see%20how%20developers%20customize%20Llama%204%20for%20their%20own%20use%20cases.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWe've%20seen%20questions%20from%20the%20community%20about%20the%20latest%20release%20of%20Llama-4%20on%20Arena.%20To%20ensure%20full%20transparency%2C%20we're%20releasing%202%2C000%2B%20head-to-head%20battle%20results%20for%20public%20review.%20This%20includes%20user%20prompts%2C%20model%20responses%2C%20and%20user%20preferences.%20(link%20in%20next%20tweet)%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EEarly%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20lmarena.ai%20(formerly%20lmsys.org)%20(%40lmarena_ai)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Flmarena_ai%2Fstatus%2F1909397817434816562%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EApril%208%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224f714870-0b8f-4897-ae19-d30a9a76fbae%5C%22%3EThe%20benchmark%20problem%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20saga%20speaks%20to%20wider%20issues%20the%20AI%20industry%20has%20increasingly%20had%20with%20benchmarks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20spending%20billions%20of%20dollars%20developing%20AI%20have%20a%20lot%20riding%20on%20releasing%20models%20that%20are%20more%20powerful%20than%20the%20last%2C%20which%20cognitive%20scientist%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-orwellian-surveillance-gary-marcus-nsa-nakasone-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20researcher%20Gary%20Marcus%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20can%20be%20problematic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNowadays%2C%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20resting%20on%20performance%20on%20benchmarks%2C%20it%20becomes%20very%20tempting%20for%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20to%20create%20training%20data%20that%20'teaches%20to%20the%20test%2C'%20and%20then%20the%20benchmarks%20tend%20to%20lose%20even%20more%20validity%2C%26quot%3B%20Marcus%2C%20who%20has%20criticized%20areas%20of%20the%20AI%20industry%20he%20sees%20as%20overhyped%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20benchmarks%20are%20measuring%20the%20right%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20February%20paper%20titled%20%26quot%3BCan%20we%20trust%20AI%20Benchmarks%3F%20An%20interdisciplinary%20review%20of%20current%20issues%20in%20AI%20evaluation%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2502.06559%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearchers%20at%20the%20European%20Commission's%20Joint%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20concluded%20that%20major%20issues%20exist%20in%20today's%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20said%20there%20are%20%26quot%3Bsystemic%20flaws%20in%20current%20benchmarking%20practices%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20are%20%26quot%3Bfundamentally%20shaped%20by%20cultural%2C%20commercial%20and%20competitive%20dynamics%20that%20often%20prioritize%20state-of-the-art%20performance%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20broader%20societal%20concerns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Dean%20Valentine%2C%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20AI%20security%20startup%20ZeroPath%2C%20said%20a%20March%20blog%20post%20that%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lesswrong.com%2Fposts%2F4mvphwx5pdsZLMmpY%2Frecent-ai-model-progress-feels-mostly-like-bullshit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERecent%20AI%20model%20progress%20feels%20mostly%20like%20bullshit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20post%2C%20Valentine%20said%20that%20he%20and%20his%20team%20had%20been%20evaluating%20the%20performance%20of%20different%20models%20claiming%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Bsome%20sort%20of%20improvement%26quot%3B%20since%20the%20release%20of%20Anthropic's%203.5%20Sonnet%20in%20June%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20new%20models%20his%20team%20tried%20had%20made%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20difference%26quot%3B%20in%20his%20company's%20internal%20benchmarks%20or%20in%20developers'%20abilities%20to%20find%20new%20bugs%2C%20he%20said.%20They%20might%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bmore%20fun%20to%20talk%20to%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20but%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bnot%20reflective%20of%20economic%20usefulness%20or%20generality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20put%20it%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20industry%20can't%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20measure%20even%20the%20intellectual%20ability%20of%20models%20now%2C%20while%20they%20are%20mostly%20confined%20to%20chatrooms%2C%26quot%3B%20it's%20hard%20to%20see%20how%20more%20complex%20AI%20could%20be%20accurately%20measured%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22961aaa06-8514-4ac9-9d57-01c81fc2f00a%5C%22%3EBenchmarks%20can%20be%20a%20'good%20compass'%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENathan%20Habib%2C%20a%20machine%20learning%20engineer%20at%20Hugging%20Face%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20problem%20with%20many%20arena-style%20benchmarks%20is%20that%20they%20skew%20towards%20human%20preference%20through%20crowdsourced%20votes%2C%20which%20means%20%26quot%3Byou%20can%20optimize%20your%20model%20for%20likability%20rather%20than%20capability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20benchmarks%20to%20truly%2