IHC%20aggregated%20information%20on%20household%20economics%20and%20demographics.%20The%20study%20found%20which%20rental%20units%20are%20affordable%20for%20each%20household%20based%20on%20the%20units'%20rent%20and%20utility%20bills%20falling%20below%2030%25%20of%20the%20household's%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20state%20has%20a%20shortage%20of%20affordable%20housing%20for%20those%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20income%20distribution%2C%20the%20worst%20being%20Nevada%20at%2017%20affordable%20rentals%20not%20already%20occupied%20by%20a%20higher-income%20household%20for%20every%20100%20extremely%20low-income%20households.%20The%20best%20being%20North%20Dakota%20at%2062%20rentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FMZqWS%2F5%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20housing%20shortage%20for%20low-income%20renters%20in%20the%20US%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20state%20of%20Massachusetts%20has%20one%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstates-most-affordable-expensive-homes-housing-supply-rising-prices-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20most%20expensive%20housing%20markets%20in%20the%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20its%20capital%20is%20ranked%20second%20for%20the%20availability%20of%20affordable%20rentals.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20three%20major%20cities%20in%20Texas%20%E2%80%94%20Houston%2C%20Dallas%2C%20and%20Austin%20%E2%80%94%20are%20listed%20among%20the%20top%20five%20cities%20with%20the%20most%20severe%20rental%20shortages%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20median%20price%20of%20a%20home%20in%20Texas%20is%20around%20%2440%2C000%20less%20than%20the%20national%20median%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20much%20easier%20and%20cheaper%20to%20build%20housi