0Science%20University%20who%20studies%20the%20oral%20microbiome%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20likened%20the%20ecosystem%20of%20the%20oral%20microbiome%20to%20a%20landscape%20following%20a%20volcanic%20eruption.%20It's%20barren%20(after%20a%20thorough%20clean)%2C%20but%20plants%20eventually%20grow%20and%20change%20the%20environment%2C%20allowing%20secondary%20plants%20such%20as%20moss%20to%20grow.%20After%20a%20few%20years%20(or%20a%20few%20days%20of%20not%20brushing%20well%20enough)%2C%20moss%20breaks%20down%20the%20rock%2C%20and%20more%20plant%20species%20emerge%2C%20until%2C%20eventually%2C%20you%20have%20a%20whole%20rainforest%20of%20microbes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20mature%20species%20of%20microbes%20are%20what%20can%20cause%20infections%20that%20break%20down%20the%20barrier%20between%20the%20gums%20and%20blood%2C%20enabling%20them%20to%20enter%20the%20bloodstream.%20That's%20why%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdental%2Fgums-bleed-when-flossing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20bleeding%20gums%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20a%20hallmark%20of%20periodontal%20disease%2C%20Baker%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20in%20the%20bloodstream%2C%20bacteria%20can%20travel%20to%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20body%20and%20cause%20damage%20and%20inflammation%2C%20he%20said.%20Gum%20disease-causing%20bacteria%20have%20been%20found%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgum-disease-health-problems-alzheimers-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrains%20of%20people%20with%20Alzheimer's%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20tumors%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-environmental-causes-microplastics-antibiotics-sleep-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%20patients%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20in%20heart%20tissue%20of%20people%20with%20cardiovascular%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20these%20microbes%20are%20causing%20chronic%20illness%2C%20cont